49
00:00:58,010 --> 00:01:00,110
Hello.

13
53
00:01:00,110 --> 00:01:01,200
Hi.

14
57
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:04,620
I'm Yang Ho Rang. We were in the same class in middle school. In second year.

15
61
00:01:04,620 --> 00:01:06,440
Yeah. I know.

16
65
00:01:06,440 --> 00:01:09,420
Actually, I wanted to be in the same class as you.

17
69
00:01:09,420 --> 00:01:11,570
You got the highest scores in our whole grade.

18
73
00:01:11,570 --> 00:01:16,200
Starting today I'll be your desk partner. Help me out so I can get my grades up, so I could be admitted to a university in Seoul, okay?

19
77
00:01:22,530 --> 00:01:24,800
But, how come

20
81
00:01:24,800 --> 00:01:26,950
you speak in Seoul dialect?

21
85
00:01:26,950 --> 00:01:28,330
What?

22
89
00:01:28,330 --> 00:01:30,670
I transferred here from Seoul. You didn't know?

23
93
00:01:30,670 --> 00:01:34,860
I know, but didn't you come when you were in kindergarten?

24
97
00:01:34,860 --> 00:01:37,980
Hey, teacher! Teacher's here.

25
101
00:01:45,900 --> 00:01:50,060
Look here, you girls, let's get our wits together here.

26
105
00:01:50,060 --> 00:01:54,660
You guys are 18 now, okay? Juniors!

27
109
00:01:54,660 --> 00:01:59,210
And as you can see, we've got a transfer student. Woo Soo Ji.

28
113
00:01:59,210 --> 00:02:02,430
She just transferred today from Jinju. Say hi.

29
117
00:02:08,830 --> 00:02:10,210
That's the end?

30
121
00:02:10,210 --> 00:02:12,050
Yes.

31
125
00:02:13,560 --> 00:02:16,430
Go and sit in that empty seat.

32
129
00:02:27,390 --> 00:02:30,010
What the heck? Is she a volleyball player?

33
133
00:02:35,110 --> 00:02:37,560
Make sure to get your parent's signature on your report cards.

34
137
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:40,210
Oh no!

35
141
00:02:41,670 --> 00:02:45,070
Ji Ho, you are first in our grade again, of course?

36
145
00:02:45,070 --> 00:02:46,970
<i>2 out of 147</i>

37
149
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:49,890
You're second?

38
153
00:02:49,890 --> 00:02:53,370
If you're second, then who's first?

39
157
00:02:53,370 --> 00:02:54,570
Wow, she's ranked first.

40
161
00:02:54,570 --> 00:02:57,340
What? Is this true?

41
165
00:02:57,340 --> 00:03:00,130
- Soo Ji, teach us how to study. 
 - Me, too.

42
170
00:03:00,130 --> 00:03:02,180
- Teach me, too. 
 - Get in line, I asked her first.

43
175
00:03:02,180 --> 00:03:05,260
Why get in line? Let's all do it together.

44
179
00:03:07,980 --> 00:03:11,980
Wow, that volleyball is ranked first in our grade?

45
183
00:03:17,430 --> 00:03:21,000
She only looks like she'd be good in volleyball. How can she be first in our grade?

46
187
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:25,260
Looks like she always ranked first back in Jinju, too.

47
191
00:03:25,260 --> 00:03:28,770
Hey, do you know why Volleyball transferred here to Namhae?

48
195
00:03:28,770 --> 00:03:31,440
I don't know. Why?

49
199
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:36,490
Her mom ran a fancy restaurant in Jinju, but with a married man...

50
203
00:03:40,780 --> 00:03:42,880
I hear that she doesn't even have a dad.

51
207
00:03:42,880 --> 00:03:46,800
Or she has one, but she doesn't know who he is, some people say.

52
211
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:50,600
Don't say such things to anyone, okay?

53
215
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:52,980
Of course not. Why would I?

54
219
00:04:07,630 --> 00:04:10,870
Aish, look at these stars.

55
223
00:04:10,870 --> 00:04:13,090
So many, like a pack of dogs.

56
227
00:04:15,940 --> 00:04:18,880
This place sucks. Out in the boonies.

57
231
00:04:28,510 --> 00:04:29,610
What's your problem?

58
235
00:04:29,610 --> 00:04:32,010
Do you want to die?

59
239
00:04:32,010 --> 00:04:35,050
No, why would I?

60
243
00:04:35,050 --> 00:04:36,310
What's wrong?

61
247
00:04:36,310 --> 00:04:40,200
I heard that you said my mom had a fancy restaurant?

62
251
00:04:41,180 --> 00:04:42,750
That's just what I heard.

63
255
00:04:42,750 --> 00:04:44,580
Oh, really?

64
259
00:04:44,580 --> 00:04:50,610
So saying my mom had an affair with a married man and ran away here? You just heard that, too?

65
263
00:04:50,610 --> 00:04:53,580
Let's go. Let's see who wins.

66
267
00:04:54,860 --> 00:04:57,330
Let go of her and talk.

67
271
00:04:58,100 --> 00:05:00,450
Jinju, let me go!

68
275
00:05:00,450 --> 00:05:03,710
Hey, let go!

69
279
00:05:10,130 --> 00:05:14,860
I was boasting so much that the first and second ranked students were both in my class.

70
283
00:05:14,860 --> 00:05:19,010
This is so embarrassing. Come to your senses already.

71
287
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:25,910
Oh, what happened, Ji Ho?

72
291
00:05:25,910 --> 00:05:29,250
Hey, you're the one who picked the fight, huh?

73
295
00:05:31,270 --> 00:05:33,290
Look at this mess. Aigoo!

74
299
00:05:33,290 --> 00:05:35,900
Can't you do better?

75
303
00:05:35,900 --> 00:05:38,000
Hey, aiyoo.

76
307
00:05:54,900 --> 00:05:58,220
Why were they only hitting me? Why only me?!?

77
311
00:05:58,220 --> 00:06:01,100
So I don't study well. Does that mean I'm not human?

78
315
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:04,820
What's so great about you two?

79
319
00:06:04,820 --> 00:06:07,570
You guys look like stuffed pancakes!

80
323
00:06:07,570 --> 00:06:10,110
You ugly girls!

81
327
00:06:15,970 --> 00:06:18,830
Ho Rang, don't cry.

82
331
00:06:18,830 --> 00:06:20,580
What's with that?

83
335
00:06:20,580 --> 00:06:23,020
You're great at the local dialect.

84
339
00:06:23,650 --> 00:06:27,930
If you think it's so unfair, then do better studying.

85
343
00:06:27,930 --> 00:06:30,960
If I could be good at studying just by wanting to do it,

86
347
00:06:30,960 --> 00:06:33,900
then I would be already good at it!

87
351
00:06:34,790 --> 00:06:36,150
What is she saying?

88
355
00:06:36,150 --> 00:06:39,710
Stop acting like you're so great! It's obnoxious!

89
359
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:48,910
Yang Ho Rang, I heard you came to my house?

90
363
00:06:50,230 --> 00:06:52,370
What is this pathetic thing?

91
367
00:06:52,370 --> 00:06:53,800
Huh?

92
371
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:56,030
Thanks for the apples. (apple = sa-gwa, is an homonym for apology)

93
375
00:06:58,700 --> 00:07:02,410
The ones I circled in red, solve those problems three times.

94
379
00:07:02,410 --> 00:07:04,590
Those will be in the mid term exams.

95
383
00:07:07,960 --> 00:07:11,760
By the way, stop using Seoul dialect in front of me.

96
387
00:07:11,760 --> 00:07:13,530
It's obnoxious.

97
391
00:07:14,450 --> 00:07:16,510
You're ridiculous, really.

98
395
00:07:24,380 --> 00:07:28,540
<i>And just like that, we became friends.</i>

99
399
00:07:28,540 --> 00:07:32,320
Look at this. I got a 70 on the math test.

100
403
00:07:33,630 --> 00:07:35,310
How's that?

101
407
00:07:35,310 --> 00:07:38,130
- Is that right? Your scores went up by a lot. 
- You did well.

102
412
00:07:39,400 --> 00:07:41,790
You only got three problems wrong.

103
416
00:07:41,790 --> 00:07:46,200
♫ <i>I smile quietly</i> ♫

104
420
