♫ <i>So no one knows, no one at all</i> ♫

105
424
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:56,360
<i> Woo Soo and Ji Ho</i>
 ♫ <i>I draw so many stars</i> ♫

106
429
00:07:56,360 --> 00:07:59,390
♫ <i>So no one knows, no one at all</i> ♫

107
433
00:07:59,390 --> 00:08:02,420
I will get you girls this time! How dare you?

108
437
00:08:02,420 --> 00:08:04,630
- Oh, I got one. I hooked one!
 - What is it?

109
442
00:08:04,630 --> 00:08:07,250
- I got one!
 - What is it?

110
447
00:08:07,250 --> 00:08:10,250
Wow, it's huge! A Black Porgy!

111
451
00:08:10,250 --> 00:08:12,380
Wow!

112
455
00:08:40,130 --> 00:08:43,540
I'm going to be president of my own company.

113
459
00:08:43,540 --> 00:08:46,170
You study so well, why would you become a merchant?

114
463
00:08:46,170 --> 00:08:50,520
Become a professor, or go work at a huge conglomerate and become a career woman.

115
467
00:08:50,520 --> 00:08:55,230
Hey, I could do that for 100 years, but I'd still be nothing but a wage-worker.

116
471
00:08:55,230 --> 00:08:59,600
We only live once. Why spend it working under someone else?

117
475
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:02,560
I want plenty of money, to my heart's content.

118
479
00:09:02,560 --> 00:09:06,290
Of course, with that personality, how could you work for anyone else?

119
483
00:09:06,290 --> 00:09:11,770
I want to marry a self-made rich man and become a homemaker.

120
487
00:09:11,770 --> 00:09:14,670
A self-made rich man?

121
491
00:09:14,670 --> 00:09:17,250
Why? Why not just marry a rich man?

122
495
00:09:17,250 --> 00:09:22,550
No way. If he inherits the wealth, I will have to be a slave to my in-laws. It's part of the price.

123
499
00:09:22,550 --> 00:09:25,200
But if a man is a self-made success, then it all becomes ours.

124
503
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:29,390
Then among us, there will be a madam with a "-sa?"

125
507
00:09:29,390 --> 00:09:32,540
Doctor or lawyer's wife? (eui-SA = doctor, byeon-ho-SA = lawyer)

126
511
00:09:32,540 --> 00:09:36,350
These days, the trend is engineering. An engineering major turned venture capitalist.

127
515
00:09:36,350 --> 00:09:40,620
That is the perfect self-made rich man I'm dreaming of.

128
519
00:09:41,990 --> 00:09:43,780
What about you, Ji Ho?

129
523
00:09:43,780 --> 00:09:47,910
It's obvious. Becoming a writer, right?

130
527
00:09:49,620 --> 00:09:51,050
No.

131
531
00:09:51,050 --> 00:09:53,380
Then, what is it?

132
535
00:09:53,380 --> 00:09:58,600
It's true that I want to become a writer because I like to write, but

133
539
00:09:58,600 --> 00:10:01,560
that isn't my dream.

134
543
00:10:01,560 --> 00:10:03,730
My dream

135
547
00:10:04,930 --> 00:10:07,220
- is love. 
 - Love?

136
552
00:10:07,220 --> 00:10:09,030
What kind of dream is love?

137
556
00:10:09,030 --> 00:10:12,850
Min Kook who lives next door to you, he likes you. Go date him.

138
560
00:10:12,850 --> 00:10:16,800
No, he's ugly. Date Seung Won instead.

139
564
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:19,310
No, I don't mean that sort of thing.

140
568
00:10:19,880 --> 00:10:24,460
That once-in-a-lifetime love.

141
572
00:10:25,490 --> 00:10:30,350
Meeting a man who is my fate,

142
576
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:32,990
that is my dream.

143
580
00:10:35,270 --> 00:10:39,770
<i> I have someone I like.</i>

144
584
00:10:39,770 --> 00:10:40,930
<i> What are you saying?</i>

145
588
00:10:40,930 --> 00:10:43,230
<i> What? Who?</i>

146
592
00:10:47,110 --> 00:10:48,830
<i> My husband.</i>

147
596
00:10:48,830 --> 00:10:50,460
<i> Hey, are you joking around?</i>

148
600
00:10:50,460 --> 00:10:53,090
<i>What's with you, Ji Ho? Are you rubbing it in?</i>

149
604
00:10:53,090 --> 00:10:55,740
<i> Then, I'm going to confess my love for Won Seok here.</i>

150
608
00:10:55,740 --> 00:10:58,250
<i> You guys... Just sleep!</i>

151
612
00:10:58,370 --> 00:11:04,810
♫ <i>please be a shelter for my tired soul</i> ♫

152
616
00:11:04,810 --> 00:11:08,290
<i>Actually what marriage really is,</i>

153
620
00:11:08,290 --> 00:11:11,600
<i>I'm still not sure.</i>

154
624
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:15,130
<i>But liking someone...</i>

155
628
00:11:15,130 --> 00:11:16,790
♫ <i>all you have to do is to give it a quick glance as you pass by</i> ♫

156
632
00:11:16,790 --> 00:11:22,150
♫ <i>all you have to do is to give it a quick glance as you pass by</i> ♫

157
636
00:11:22,150 --> 00:11:24,900
♫ <i>in the midst of the morning fog, it stopped</i> ♫

158
640
00:11:24,900 --> 00:11:28,630
<i>Love, if you have just one in life,</i>

159
644
00:11:29,780 --> 00:11:31,800
<i>it is plenty. </i>

160
648
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:37,170
<i>That one comment of his circled all around my heart.</i>

161
652
00:11:38,840 --> 00:11:45,020
♫ <i>The little petal that is blossoming again</i> ♫

162
656
00:11:46,930 --> 00:11:51,240
♫ <i>Shall we go looking for the morning sun?</i> ♫

163
660
00:11:51,240 --> 00:11:54,200
<i>Even the back of his head</i>

164
664
00:11:55,700 --> 00:11:58,230
<i>looks dashing to me.</i>

165
668
00:12:03,620 --> 00:12:06,890
Oh, you're up.

166
672
00:12:06,890 --> 00:12:08,920
Yes.

167
676
00:12:08,920 --> 00:12:11,290
Is Kitty better?

168
680
00:12:11,290 --> 00:12:16,490
Yes. I think it's like the clinic said, just temporary.

169
684
00:12:24,970 --> 00:12:26,870
What?

170
688
00:12:26,870 --> 00:12:29,510
Is something on my face?

171
692
00:12:29,510 --> 00:12:33,540
<i>Yes. Handsomeness.</i>

172
696
00:12:36,760 --> 00:12:40,430
Is something on the window?

173
700
00:12:40,430 --> 00:12:42,890
Maybe I need to do some cleaning.

174
704
00:12:49,930 --> 00:12:53,870
♫ <i>Even if you don't want love</i> ♫

175
708
00:12:53,870 --> 00:12:58,040
<i>To be able to see the person you like every day. </i>

176
712
00:12:58,040 --> 00:13:03,180
<i>Marriage is something </i>

177
716
00:13:03,180 --> 00:13:04,820
<i>that is so nice.</i>

178
720
00:13:04,820 --> 00:13:08,240
♫ <i>it makes me want to be in love</i> ♫

179
724
00:13:10,870 --> 00:13:13,140
So you guys were home.

180
728
00:13:13,140 --> 00:13:15,100
Mother!

181
732
00:13:22,220 --> 00:13:25,770
<i>Episode 10
 - Because It's My First Time In "Sea" (In-Law's) World</i>

182
737
00:13:26,430 --> 00:13:29,910
This is pickled deodeok roots, and this is braised mackerel.

183
741
00:13:29,910 --> 00:13:32,520
He really loves braised fish.

184
745
00:13:32,520 --> 00:13:33,940
I see.

185
749
00:13:33,940 --> 00:13:35,740
What brings you here without even calling first.

186
753
00:13:35,740 --> 00:13:38,860
It's my son's home. Why would I call first?

187
757
00:13:38,860 --> 00:13:42,080
I came because I thought you guys would be home for sure since it's the weekend.

188
761
00:13:42,080 --> 00:13:44,500
Let's put these in the fridge.

189
765
00:13:44,500 --> 00:13:45,920
Oh, yes.

190
769
00:13:45,920 --> 00:13:47,000
Let me do it.

191
773
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:51,150
It's alright. Like you know anything about kitchen stuff.

192
777
00:13:51,150 --> 00:13:53,920
Homemaking is done by the experts.

193
781
00:13:53,920 --> 00:13:55,500
Right, Ji Ho?

194
785
00:13:55,500 --> 00:13:57,000
Yes.

195
789
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:59,450
- This. 
- Yes, give to me, please.

196
794
00:14:20,540 --> 00:14:25,390
You remember Vice Principal Hwang, right? He sent a box of apples.

197
798
00:14:25,390 --> 00:14:28,390
I tried them with your father-in-law and they're so delicious.

198
802
00:14:28,390 --> 00:14:29,090
Yes.

199
806
00:14:29,090 --> 00:14:31,790
Does our daughter-in-law like apples too?

200
810
00:14:31,790 --> 00:14:33,410
Yes, I like them.

201
814
00:14:33,410 --> 00:14:35,820
Well, actually, I'm not picky about any food.

202
818
00:14:35,820 --> 00:14:38,600
That's great.

203
822
00:14:45,950 --> 00:14:47,930
Let me take it, plea--

204
826
00:14:50,550 --> 00:14:52,730
Give to me. I'll do it.

205
830
00:14:57,790 --> 00:15:00,130
I hear our Ji Ho works at a cafe?

206
834
00:15:00,130 --> 00:15:02,580
Yes. I thought I should do some work.

207
838
00:15:02,580 --> 00:15:04,860
In case it's hard for Oppa to have to do all the work?

208
842
00:15:04,860 --> 00:15:08,140
Oh, you're so lovely.

209
846
00:15:08,140 --> 00:15:10,970
Where did he find such a nice girl to bring home?

210
850
00:15:12,750 --> 00:15:15,250
You know tomorrow's the memorial, right?

211
854
00:15:15,250 --> 00:15:18,260
- If you get off work early--
 - I don't get off early.

212
859
00:15:18,260 --> 00:15:21,720
And did I ever go to the memorial before? Why suddenly--

213
863
00:15:21,720 --> 00:15:24,810
Alright. I know you're busy.

214
867
00:15:24,810 --> 00:15:29,100
I mean, if you have time, try to come, that's all I'm saying.

215
871
00:15:31,100 --> 00:15:33,270
Let me have that.

216
875
00:15:33,270 --> 00:15:35,360
Like you're really going to peel an apple.

217
879
00:15:35,360 --> 00:15:37,920
This is also for people who have experience doing it.

218
883
00:15:37,920 --> 00:15:39,920
Right?

219
887
00:15:39,920 --> 00:15:41,450
Yes.

220
891
00:15:44,570 --> 00:15:45,980
Please give it to me. I'll do it.

221
895
00:15:45,980 --> 00:15:48,100
Will you?

222
899
00:15:51,130 --> 00:15:55,630
<i>Ji Ho, we're here already. When are you coming? </i>

223
903
00:15:56,270 --> 00:16:00,160
You said you had an appointment, right? With your friends.

224
907
00:16:00,160 --> 00:16:01,610
Oh.

